// Test error when an immutable record/list update is discarded
// (e.g. r.f = 1 without assigning the result)

r = { a: 1, b: 2 }
r.a = 10  // ERROR

lst = [1, 2, 3]
lst[0] = 99 // ERROR

mp = %{"x" => 10}
mp["x"] = 20 // ERROR

// Assignment with usage is valid, but the discarded updates above should cause analysis to fail
// before execution.
print("Should not print")
